   "source": [
    "### 📊 I can accept the normality (H0)\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Problem:** Our `product_quality` scores were skewed and failed the normality test. it was so close with 0.028 .\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Fix (Box-Cox & Lambda):** We used a **Box-Cox transformation**, an algorithm that automatically tests different mathematical powers to bend the data into a perfect bell curve. The specific power it chose as the winner is called **Lambda ($\\lambda$)**. For our data, $\\lambda = 1.3160$. even the BOXCOX made it closer with .047 which we can consider a pass.\n",
    "\n",
    "**The Result:** More importantly, when we split the data by `firm_size` (which is what MANOVA cares about), both the Small and Large firm groups passed the normality test perfectly ($p > 0.05$). \n"
   ]
  },
